Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant De'aiso Assunta Bell in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Katrina Voge appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  De'aiso Assunta Bell appeared by video means.

Defendant De'aiso Assunta Bell in court via Zoom with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  
Katrina Voge appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Pretrial conference held.  Defendant has a pending felony in Br. 2 and requests a status date after the felony case's next court date.  Case is adjourned to Br. 1.  Status conference scheduled for August 8, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Case is scheduled for a pre-trial conference on 6/27/2022. Due to a scheduling conflict with Defense counsel, case is rescheduled to 7/22/2022 at 1:30pm.
Court ordered him not to drive in any cars that he doesn't know the people.
Court ordered arrest warrant withdrawn.  Recall issued.

Defendant De'aiso Assunta Bell in court.  Student Intern Caroline Pellegrini under the supervision of Stephan Eduard Nolten appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant advised that this case is assigned to Judge Davila, Branch 01.
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Defendant IS Public Defender eligible. Defendant is ordered to provide the public defender's office with the next court date.  
The case is adjourned to Br. 01 for a Pretrial Conference.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for June 27, 2022 at 09:00 am.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE ARREST WARRANT.

Defendant De'aiso Assunta Bell not in court.  Alexander C. Dyer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered an Arrest Warrant to be issued. Upon arrest, defendant is ordered remanded to a commissioner. Court ordered any bail on deposit to be forfeited. Court makes a finding that there is a possible victim identified and stays the forfeiture order with restitution to be determined at close of case.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 06/08/2022@2p
